Clarke Wins British Open Golf by Three Strokes Over Mickelson, Johnson

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-07-17T17:05:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-17/clarke-wins-british-open-golf-by-three-strokes-over-mickelson-johnson.html
Northern Ireland ’s Darren Clarke won
the British Open by three shots for his first major golf
championship.  Clarke, 42, shot even-par 70 today at Royal St. George’s in
Sandwich,  England , to finish with a score of 5-under 275.  Americans  Dustin Johnson  and  Phil Mickelson  tied for second
at 2-under.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  